<item>
            <title>[JCR-2546] SISM blocks the item state cache when loading a new item</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2546</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The SharedItemStateManager.getNonVirtualItemState() method contains a loadItemState() call within a &amp;quot;synchronized (cache)&amp;quot; block. This prevents all item state cache access while a new item is being loaded from the persistence manager. I have at least one case where this has caused a serious performance drop, essentially synchronizing repository access for all readers.</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12458243">JCR-2546</key>
            <summary>SISM blocks the item state cache when loading a new item</summary>
